May 1 at 12:37 PM ·

Free Meals for Children Under 18!

Starting Monday, May 4th, every Monday and Wednesday from 12:00 PM - 2:00 PM Free Grab-and-Go Meals will be provided to parents who have children under 18 years old.
A total of 6 meals will be provided per child- 3 for breakfast and 3 for lunch. This also includes 6 pints of milk per child.

Parents, please bring I.D. and please wear a mask.
The Lighthouse
141 W Somerset Ave Phila PA 19133

#TheLighthouse1893 #TheLighthouseFamilySchool #COVID19 #FreeMeals #GrabAndGoMeals

post_text:
Fighter Jet Flyover Today!

ECCS Family!
The Air Force Thunderbirds and Navy Blue Angles Demonstration flight teams will fly over our area today to show support for our first responders, medical professionals, and all those on the front lines of the COVID-19 battle.

These flight teams normally fly at air shows around the country and perform amazing aerial tricks!

They should be entering the Philadelphia area right around 1:55 pm should be in the area for 20 mins. This will be happening shortly after the Staff Talent Show today. All are encouraged to keep an eye out for this amazing event!

See the graphic below to see when they will be in your area.
#NavyBlueAngels #AirForceThunderbirds #FLYOVER

post_text:
As part of Esperanza’s longstanding commitment to strengthening the Hispanic community, we want to ensure that you have the information you need to TAKE ACTION and BE COUNTED. We are proud to be one of many Philly Counts2020 Action Fund partners working together to make sure YOU are represented in this year’s Census.

Como parte del largo compromiso de Esperanza de fortalecer la comunidad hispana, queremos asegurarnos de que tengan la información necesaria para que TOMEN ACCCIÓN y SEAN CONTADOS. Nos enorgullece ser uno de los muchos colaboradores junto a Philly Counts2020 Action Fund Partners, para asegurarnos de que TÚ estés representado en el censo de este año.

post_text: Our Hope Tree🌳 “We see our organization this year as a tree. The ECCS staff members act as the roots, grounding and supporting our students. The trunk, which builds students up in their growth, is made up of how we want them to feel at our school. The branches represent the strategies and skills we want to instill in our students. And the students themselves are the leaves! We look forward to a year full of growth!” - Jessica Pedlow - ECCS Teacher

post_text: These two ladies right are another piece of the puzzle that make ECCS great. Thank you to Dr. Faulkner-Beitzel(left) and Mrs. Bustamante (right) for all you do. In regards to International Women's History Month, Dr. Faulkner-Beitzel states “My great great grandmother was a suffragette in Ohio. I grew up with women who felt a sense of duty to do better, for their families and communities. International Women’s History Month to me is the celebration of the power of a girl who feels she can change the world through knowledge, hard work, advocating for equity, and love for all people.” 🙌🏻🙌🏼🙌🏽🙌🏾🙌🏿 💪#celebratewomen #womenshistorymonth #eccs #Esperanzacyber
